a first rupturable plate(40)blocking a first communication passage (38)between the pressurized gas chamber (20) and the combustion chamber (30); 
a second rupturable plate (58) blocking a second communication passage (56) between the pressurized gas chamber (20) and the diffuser portion (50); and 
afilter (60) disposed and positioned in the pressurized gas chamber (20) to cover the second rupturable plate (58), 
the filter (60) allowing, during actuation, the combustion gas from the combustion chamber (30) and the pressurized gas to pass therethrough and be discharged therefrom in response to rupturing the second rupturable plate (58).

description.p:
Invention 1 of the present invention provides
a gas generator(10) inflating an air bag,
the gas generator(10) including:
a pressurized gas chamber(20) having an outer shell formed by a cylindrical pressurized gas chamber housing (22), the pressurized gas chamber being filled with pressurized gas;
a combustion chamber(30) connected to a first end portion of the pressurized gas chamber(20) and including an ignition device(34) and the gas generating agent(36) accommodated in a combustion chamber housing(32);
a diffuser portion(50) connected to a second end portion of the pressurized gas chamber (20) and provided with a gas discharge port (52);
a first rupturable plate(40) blocking a first communication passage(38) between the pressurized gas chamber(20) and the combustion chamber(30);
a second rupturable plate(58) blocking a second communication passage(56) between the pressurized gas chamber(20) and the diffuser portion (50); and
afilter(60) disposed and positioned in the pressurized gas chamber(20) to cover the second rupturable plate(58),
the filter(60) allowing, during actuation, the combustion gas from the combustion chamber(30) and the pressurized gas to pass therethrough and be discharged therefrom in response to rupturing the second rupturable plate(58).

Inveniton 2 of the present invention provides,
a gas generator (10) inflating an air bag by combustion gas generated by combustion of a gas generating agent(36) and pressurized gas,
the gas generator(10) including:
a pressurized gas chamber(20) having an outer shell formed by a cylindrical pressurized gas chamber housing (22), being filled with the pressurized gas;
a combustion chamber(30) connected to a first end portion of the pressurized gas chamber(20) and including an ignition device(34) and a gas generating agent(36) accommodated in a combustion chamber housing (32);
a diffuser portion(150) connected to a second end portion of the pressurized gas chamber(20),
the diffuser portion(150) being in a cap-like shape including a closed end surface(151a), a peripheral surface (151b) having a plurality of gas discharge ports (152), a flange portion (151c) at an opening thereof and a cylindrical supporting wall(160) protruding toward the pressurized gas chamber(20) on an annular surface(153) of the flange portion(151c), facing the pressurized gas chamber(20);
a first rupturable plate(40) blocking a first communication passage(38) between the pressurized gas chamber(20) and the combustion chamber(30);
a second rupturable plate(58) blocking a second communication passage(56) between the pressurized gas chamber(20) and the diffuser portion(150);
a cup member (170) accommodating a filter (60), disposed in the pressurized gas chamber(20) to cover the second rupturable plate (58) from the inside of the pressurized gas chamber(20),
the cup member(170) including a bottom surface(171) and a peripheral surface(172) having a plurality of communication holes(173) serving as a gas passage,
the cup member(170) being fixed by being fitted to an outer peripheral surface(161) of the cylindrical supporting wall(160) from the outside; and
the filter(60) having a second end surface (62) abutted against the bottom surface(171) of the cup member(170), a peripheral surface(63) abutted against the peripheral surface (172) of the cup member, and a peripheral edge portion of a first end surface(61) abutted against an annular top portion (163) at a tip of the cylindrical supporting wall(160),
thefilter(60) allowing, during actuation, combustion gas from the combustion chamber (30) and pressurized gas to pass therethrough and be discharge therefrom when the second ruptruable plate(58) is broken.

