Invention 4 of the present invention provides,
a gas generator (10) inflating an air bag by combustion gas generated by combustion of a gas generating agent(36) and pressurized gas,
the gas generator(10) including:
a pressurized gas chamber(20) having an outer shell formed by a cylindrical pressurized gas chamber housing (22), being filled with the pressurized gas;
a combustion chamber(30) connected to a first end portion of the pressurized gas chamber(20) and including an ignition device(34) and a gas generating agent(36) accommodated in a combustion chamber housing(32);
a diffuser portion(150) connected to a second end portion of the pressurized gas chamber(20),
the diffuser portion (250) being in a cap-like shape including a closed end surface(251a), a peripheral surface (251b) having a plurality of gas discharge ports (252), a flange portion (251c) at an opening thereof and a cylindrical supporting wall (260) protruding toward the pressurized gas chamber(20) on an annular surface(253) of the flange portion(251c), facing the pressurized gas chamber(20);
the cylindrical supporting wall(260) obtained by integrating, in a thickness direction, an outer cylindrical wall port ion (261) and an inner cylindrical wall port ion (262) which is lower than the outer cylindrical wall portion, including an inner annular stepped surface(263) formed by a level difference between the outer cylindrical wall portion(261) and the inner cylindrical wall portion(262);
a first rupturable plate(40) blocking a first communication passage(38) between the pressurized gas chamber(20) and the combustion chamber(30);
a second rupturable plate(58) blocking a second communication passage(56) between the pressurized gas chamber(20) and the diffuser portion(250);
acupmember (270) accommodating a filter (60), disposed in the pressurized gas chamber (20) to directly face the second rupturable plate(58) from the inside of the pressurized gas chamber(20),
the cup member(270) including a bottom surface (271), having a plurality of communication holes(272) serving as a gas passage, and a peripheral surface(273),
the cup member(270) being provided such that a peripheral edge portion of the bottom surface (271) is abutted against the inner annular stepped surface(263) of the cylindrical supporting wall(260), and an annular portion of a peripheral surface(273) in contact with the bottom surface(271) is abutted against an inner peripheral surface(261a) of the outer cylindrical wall portion(261), and
the filter(60) having a first end surface(61) abutted against the bottom surface(271) of the cup member, a peripheral surface(63) abutted against the peripheral surface (273) of the cup member, and an outer peripheral edge portion of a second end surface (62) fixed by inwardly bending a claw portion(274) formed on the peripheral surface(273) at an opening of the cup member(270); and
the filter(60) allowing, during actuation, combustion gas from the combustion chamber (30) and pressurized gas to pass therethrough and be discharged therefrom when the second ruptruable plate(58) is broken.

